<problem display_name="Where does it go? 2" linenum="73" tex_filename="./block1/lineartransformationsinRn.tex" showanswer="finished" attempts="1" rerandomize="per_student">
  <text>
    <p>
Consider the following image. </p>
    <center>
      <img src="/static/images/c1s8imageunderlintrans.svg" width="400 px" style="margin: 10px 25px 25px 25px; border:0px"/>
    </center>
    <p>
When we apply the linear transformation [mathjaxinline]T: \mathbb R^2 \rightarrow \mathbb R^2[/mathjaxinline] given by [mathjaxinline]T(x) = \left[ \begin{array}{cc} 0.5 &amp;  0 \\ 0 &amp;  2 \end{array} \right][/mathjaxinline] to the image, which picture is the result? </p>
    <center>
      <img src="/static/images/c1s8imageunderlintransAB2.svg" width="400 px" style="margin: 10px 25px 25px 25px; border:0px"/>
    </center>
    <p>
      <optionresponse>
        <optioninput options="('A','B')" correct="B"/>
      </optionresponse>
    </p>
    <p>
      <solution>
        <font color="blue">Answer: </font>
        <font color="blue">
          <p>
We see that </p>
          <table id="a0000000068" class="equation" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="7" style="table-layout:auto">
            <tr>
              <td class="equation" style="width:80%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;border-style:hidden">[mathjax]T\Bigg(\left[ \begin{array}{c} a\\ b\end{array} \right]\Bigg)=\left[ \begin{array}{cc} 0.5 &amp;  0 \\ 0 &amp;  2 \end{array} \right]\left[ \begin{array}{c} a\\ b\end{array}\right]=\left[ \begin{array}{c} 0.5a\\ 2b\end{array}\right],[/mathjax]</td>
              <td class="eqnnum" style="width:20%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:left;border-style:hidden"/>
            </tr>
          </table>
          <p>
 and thus scales the original image by a factor of 0.5 in the [mathjaxinline]x[/mathjaxinline] direction and a factor of 2 in the [mathjaxinline]y[/mathjaxinline] direction. </p>
        </font>
      </solution>
    </p>
  </text>
</problem>
